!CHAPTER Handling Edges

!SECTION Create an edge

`POST /system/gharial/graph-name/edge/collection-name`*(create an edge)*

!SUBSECTION URL parameters

`graph-name (string, required)`  
The name of the graph.

`collection-name (string, required)`  
The name of the edge collection the edge belongs to.

!SUBSECTION Description

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_create_info -->

Creates a new edge in the collection.
Within the body the has to contain a *\_from* and *\_to* value referencing to valid vertices in the graph.
Furthermore the edge has to be valid in the definition of this edge collection.

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_create_http_examples -->

```
unix> curl -X POST --data-binary @- --dump - http://localhost:8529/system/gharial/social/edge/relation
{"type":"friend","_from":"female/alice","_to":"female/diana"}

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
content-type: application/json
etag: 543501814

{ 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 201, 
  "edge" : { 
    "_id" : "relation/543501814", 
    "_rev" : "543501814", 
    "_key" : "543501814" 
  } 
}

```

!SECTION Get an edge

`GET /system/gharial/graph-name/edge/collection-name/edge-key`*(get an edge)*

!SUBSECTION URL parameters

`graph-name (string, required)`  
The name of the graph.

`collection-name (string, required)`  
The name of the edge collection the edge belongs to.

`edge-key (string, required)`  
The `_key` attribute of the edge.

!SUBSECTION Description

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_get_info -->

Gets an edge from the given collection.

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_get_http_examples -->

```
unix> curl --dump - http://localhost:8529/system/gharial/social/vertex/relation/aliceAndBob

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
content-type: application/json
etag: 546188790

{ 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 200, 
  "vertex" : { 
    "_id" : "relation/aliceAndBob", 
    "_rev" : "546188790", 
    "_key" : "aliceAndBob", 
    "_from" : "female/alice", 
    "_to" : "male/bob", 
    "type" : "married" 
  } 
}

```

!SECTION Modify an edge

`PATCH /system/gharial/graph-name/edge/collection-name/edge-key`*(modify an edge)*

!SUBSECTION URL parameters

`graph-name (string, required)`  
The name of the graph.

`collection-name (string, required)`  
The name of the edge collection the edge belongs to.

`edge-key (string, required)`  
The `_key` attribute of the edge.

!SUBSECTION Description

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_modify_info -->

Updates the data of the specific edge in the collection.

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_modify_http_examples -->

```
unix> curl -X PATCH --data-binary @- --dump - http://localhost:8529/system/gharial/social/vertex/relation/aliceAndBob
{"since":"01.01.2001"}

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
content-type: application/json
etag: 555494902

{ 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 200, 
  "vertex" : { 
    "_id" : "relation/aliceAndBob", 
    "_rev" : "555494902", 
    "_oldRev" : "554053110", 
    "_key" : "aliceAndBob" 
  } 
}

```

!SECTION Replace an edge

`PATCH /system/gharial/graph-name/edge/collection-name/edge-key`*(replace an edge)*

!SUBSECTION URL parameters

`graph-name (string, required)`  
The name of the graph.

`collection-name (string, required)`  
The name of the edge collection the edge belongs to.

`edge-key (string, required)`  
The `_key` attribute of the edge.

!SUBSECTION Description

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_replace_info -->

Replaces the data of an edge in the collection.

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_replace_http_examples -->

```
unix> curl -X PUT --data-binary @- --dump - http://localhost:8529/system/gharial/social/vertex/relation/aliceAndBob
{"type":"divorced"}

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
content-type: application/json
etag: 551366134

{ 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 200, 
  "vertex" : { 
    "_id" : "relation/aliceAndBob", 
    "_rev" : "551366134", 
    "_oldRev" : "550055414", 
    "_key" : "aliceAndBob" 
  } 
}

```

!SECTION Remove an edge

`DELETE /system/gharial/graph-name/edge/collection-name/edge-key`*(remove an edge)*

!SUBSECTION URL parameters

`graph-name (string, required)`  
The name of the graph.

`collection-name (string, required)`  
The name of the edge collection the edge belongs to.

`edge-key (string, required)`  
The `_key` attribute of the edge.

!SUBSECTION Description

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_delete_info -->

Removes an edge from the collection.

<!-- @startDocuBlock JSF_general_graph_edge_delete_http_examples -->

```
unix> curl -X DELETE --dump - http://localhost:8529/system/gharial/social/vertex/relation/aliceAndBob

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
content-type: application/json

{ 
  "error" : false, 
  "code" : 200, 
  "vertex" : true 
}

```
